8859	\begin{lemma}
8860	[Alternating-sum assembly of the core comparison square]
8861	  \label{lem:coreIso_comm_sum}
8862	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.coreIso_comm_sum}
8863	  \uses{lem:coreIso_comm_coface, lem:section_cech_objd_apply, lem:section_cech_product_equiv}
8864	  With the notation of Lemma~\ref{lem:coreIso_obj_iso}, for each degree \(p\) the full
8865	  alternating-coface differentials are intertwined by the object isomorphisms:
8866	  \[
8867	    (\mathrm{objIso}\,p).\mathrm{hom} \cdot d^p_{\check{\mathcal{C}}(\mathcal{U}')}
8868	      \;=\;
8869	    d^p_{(G_V\circ\Psi)\check{\mathcal{C}}(\mathcal{U})} \cdot (\mathrm{objIso}\,(p+1)).\mathrm{hom}.
8870	  \]
8871	\end{lemma}
8872	\begin{proof}
8873	  \uses{lem:coreIso_comm_coface, lem:section_cech_objd_apply, lem:section_cech_product_equiv}
8874	  Both differentials are the alternating coface sums \(d^p = \sum_{k=0}^{p+1} (-1)^k
8875	  \delta_k\) (the \(\operatorname{objD}\) of the alternating-coface-map complex). Work
8876	  elementwise: by Lemma~\ref{lem:section_cech_objd_apply}, read through the product equivalence
8877	  (Lemma~\ref{lem:section_cech_product_equiv}), each side — evaluated at an element of the source
8878	  and at a coordinate \(\sigma'\) — is the pointwise finite sum \(\sum_{k} (-1)^k\,(\cdots)_k\) of
8879	  the same shape. The two sums agree summand by summand: the \(k\)-th summands carry the same sign
8880	  \((-1)^k\) and, by the per-coface square of Lemma~\ref{lem:coreIso_comm_coface}, the same coface
8881	  contribution. A termwise comparison (Finset sum congruence) of the two alternating sums
8882	  therefore yields equality of the differentials, discharging every degree at once. Stating the
8883	  match elementwise this way sidesteps the categorical
8884	  \(\operatorname{comp\_sum}/\operatorname{map\_sum}\) manipulations, which clash with the bundled
8885	  \(\mathrm{AddCommGrp}\)-hom representation of \(\operatorname{objD}\).
8886	\end{proof}
